 creative practices that would become cornerstones of media fan reception and queer belonging.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFans (Persons)zUnited Statesy20th century. 0aHomosexuality and motion pictures. 0aLesbianismzUnited Statesy20th century. 0aMotion pictures and women. 0aYoung womenzUnited Statesy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520971295?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520971295423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520971295/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY